00:11.230 --> 00:12.980
<i>When you return, are
you going to explain to Peter</i>

00:13.066 --> 00:14.698
what it is you're trying
to accomplish here?

00:14.784 --> 00:16.784
A Nassau
that can self-govern.

00:16.819 --> 00:18.579
This is not a man
that we can negotiate with,

00:18.621 --> 00:20.237
- that I can negotiate with.
- Of course you can.

00:20.323 --> 00:23.374
Because you will have just presented
him with his only daughter.

00:23.459 --> 00:25.659
I can only scavenge
leads for so long.

00:25.711 --> 00:28.162
I have an appetite for
something larger than that.

00:28.214 --> 00:30.414
<i>For this, I need
a partner I can trust.</i>

00:30.500 --> 00:32.750
<i>A launch landed on
the beach a short while ago.</i>

00:32.835 --> 00:35.219
They told Flint the gold was gone.
What did they tell you?

00:35.304 --> 00:37.388
The Urca gold
is on that beach.

00:37.473 --> 00:40.007
<i>It is almost
entirely undefended.</i>

00:40.059 --> 00:43.310
Do you know of a crew who might be
willing to aid in this endeavor?

00:43.346 --> 00:45.146
<i>Abigail, you are
no longer a hostage.</i>

00:45.181 --> 00:46.461
<i>I'm going to
get you out of here.</i>

00:46.482 --> 00:47.681
<i>So, what's the plan?</i>

00:47.767 --> 00:49.100
Leave me to answer
for this among the men?

00:49.185 --> 00:53.737
My death sentence.
You will hear from me again.

00:53.823 --> 00:56.574
- You're Captain Flint?
<i>-  My name is James.</i>

00:56.659 --> 00:58.075
James McGraw.

